INCLUDED FILES
==============
lab4c.c
	Source file containing client programs to record temperature on Beaglebone and report logs to server. If compiled to lab4c_tcp, the program uses TCP sockets to connect to the server. If compiled to lab4c_tls, the program uses TLS in addition to the socket to securely communicate with the server.

Makefile
	Specifies targets to make both executable versions, clean directory, and make tarball for distribution.

README
	This file. Includes description about included files and resources used.


RESOURCES USED
==============
For general documentation in using the OpenSSL SSL/TLS library
https://www.openssl.org/docs/manmaster/man7/ssl.html

To refresh on sockets
https://www.tutorialspoint.com/unix_sockets/socket_client_example.htm
